@startuml server-structure-overview-ver2
package "Server (Node.js)" {
    component "Main Server Logic" as ServerLogic
    component "Routes/Endpoints" as Endpoints
    component "Middleware" as Middleware
    component "Authentication" as Auth
    component "File Handling (GridFS)" as GridFS
    component "Database (MongoDB)" as Database
}

package "Client" {
    actor "User" as User
}

User --> ServerLogic : Interacts with
ServerLogic --> Endpoints : Routes user requests
ServerLogic --> Middleware : Processes data and checks permissions
ServerLogic --> Auth : Verifies user identity (JWT)
ServerLogic --> Database : Reads/writes user data
ServerLogic --> GridFS : Handles file uploads/downloads

note right of Auth
  Verifies user identity using
  JSON Web Tokens (JWT) for secure
  authentication and session handling.
end note

note right of GridFS
  Handles storage and retrieval of large
  documents and media files efficiently.
end note

note right of Database
  Stores user data, logs, and application
  data required for business logic.
end note

note bottom of Middleware
  Includes:
  - Request validation
  - Error handling
  - Logging mechanisms
end note

@enduml
